{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T06:36:16.432Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on the official Anthropic documentation and technical resources, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Tool definitions: screenshot, click, type, scroll, key\""},{"type":"text","text":" in Computer Use Architecture refers to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"the structured action commands that Claude returns when using the computer use tool"},{"type":"text","text":", defining exactly what visual interactions the agent can perform with a computer interface at the pixel level."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core Tool Definition"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Computer Use Tool"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Python: Define computer use tool\ntool = {\n    \"type\": \"computer_20241022\",\n    \"name\": \"computer\",\n    \"display_width_px\": 1024,    # Display dimensions\n    \"display_height_px\": 768\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Capabilities"},{"type":"text","text":": \"This tool provides: Screenshot capture, Mouse control (click, drag, move), Keyboard input (type text and shortcuts)\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Five Action Types"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"screenshot"},{"type":"text","text":" - Capture Screen State"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"action\": \"screenshot\"\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Purpose"},{"type":"text","text":": Capture the current screen state as a base64-encoded image."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Usage"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Takes screenshot of entire display\n- Returns image for Claude to analyze\n- Frequency: Every action cycle in the loop"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technical details"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Abstract interface\nscreenshot = await computer.screenshot()  # base64 image"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"click"},{"type":"text","text":" - Mouse Click at Coordinates"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"action\": \"click\",\n  \"coordinate\": [342, 156],  // (x, y) pixels\n  \"button\": \"left\"  // \"left\", \"right\", \"middle\"\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mouse Click Types"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Action"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Description"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"left_click"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Single click at position"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":